         <abstract>
            <p>Various algebraic reductions are made to facilitate computer verification of the following result: If $x$ and $y$ are $8 \times 8$ matrices such that $\lbrack x, y \rbrack$ is regular, $\operatorname{tr}(x) = 0$, and, with respect to the canonical symplectic involution, $x$ is symmetric and $y$ is antisymmetric, then the element $(x + \lbrack x, y \rbrack x \lbrack x, y \rbrack^{-1})^2$ satisfies a minimal equation of degree $\leqslant 2$.</p>
          </abstract>
